In the world of traditional archery,
precision, comfort, and craftsmanship
are essential. Vermil’s Padauk Wood
Thumb Rings bring these elements
together in a way that redefines what
archery gear can achieve. Designed for
archers of all levels, these rings
combine natural beauty with advanced
craftsmanship, offering an unparalleled
shooting experience.
Why Padauk Wood Stands Out
Lightweight and Luxurious
One of the most significant advantages of Padauk wood is its
weight. Vermil’s Padauk rings are 20% lighter than their resin
counterparts, making them easier to control and more
comfortable to use during long shooting sessions. But it’s not just
about performance—Padauk’s natural reddish-brown tones and
intricate grain patterns exude a sense of luxury and uniqueness,
ensuring no two rings are ever the same.
Strength Meets Elegance
Padauk wood offers the perfect balance between density and
strength. It’s sturdy enough to withstand the pressure of thumb
release while remaining lightweight for effortless handling. Its
natural resistance to moisture further enhances its durability,
ensuring your ring stays beautiful and functional over time.

A Customized Experience for Every Archer
Vermil’s Padauk Thumb Rings come in various designs, each tailored to meet specific shooting
styles and preferences. Whether you’re a beginner exploring the thumb release technique or a
seasoned archer perfecting your craft, there’s a design that matches your needs. With options
ranging in weight, grip, and shape, you’ll find a ring that complements your technique and
enhances your performance.
How to Care for Your Padauk Thumb Ring
To maintain the beauty and functionality of your ring:
1. Clean regularly: Use a dry cloth to remove dirt or moisture after each use.
2. Avoid excessive humidity: Store your ring in a dry place to prevent unnecessary
exposure to moisture.
3. Reapply beeswax: If the ring begins to feel dry, applying a layer of natural beeswax
will restore its finish and protect it from wear.
